div.div:
REGISTER AN NSI REQUEST
if: [Arguments=∅
& new valid NSI request >= NRID available]
state: [(pmin,pmax):=next valid NSI request >= NRID,
NRID:=(next valid request >= NRID).ID + 1,
pnext:=pmin]
Out: [Applog("New request {pmin}, {pmax}")]

div.div:
PROCESS AN H FILE
if: [Arguments={"period"=preq, "file"=...}
& preq >= pnext
& preq < pmax]
state: [pmin, pmax, NRID,
pnext':=pnext+1]
Out: [Applog("Processed request {pmin}, {pmax}, current {pnext}, skipped {pnext..preq-1}")]

div.div:
Legend:
if: [...]: This transition is only taken if fulfilled.
state: [...]: Variables available in the next state (persisted to disk).
Out: [...]: Created Topic data.
If in the enclave an exception is thrown during processing, then out data is not created, the instance state is "Failed" and the transition is not taken, i.e. it remains in the old state.
If no transition can be taken (too many Arguments, conditions not matching), the enclave throws an exception and the instance state is "Failed".
The application log messages are exemplay. However, they show that one can extract the period range.
